HEADWORD: Interaxis
<hw>In`ter*ax"is</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Interaxes</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <fld>(Arch.)</fld> <def>The
space between two axes. See <er>Axis</er>, 6.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The doors, windows, niches, and the like, are then placed
centrally in the <qex>interaxes</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Gwilt.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

